#-Function--msg.err
  Function: msg.err
      Desc: output an error message, with option to write to systemd journal.
          : message is coloured red on terminals.
  Synopsis: msg.err [log] string [string ...]
          : 'log'   if specified, write log entry to journal err.
          : string  write string/s to stderr.
   Example: msg.err log "Sir!" "I think you better come here."
    Source: /usr/share/okusi/entities/entities.bash
#-Function--msg.err-----------------------------------------------------------
